remixed_from.title: PG35L Micro Extruder V2 - For J-Head

title: PG35L Micro Extruder V3 - For J-Head

description.text:
Version 3 is an alternative to the TrinityLabs micro-extruder body.  This version has integrated bearing to appose idler tension. Use of the external bearing is no longer needed. The body is stronger and has M3 nut slots that don't penetrate the entire body.  Also, this body has a snap-in slot for a J-Head hot end which eliminates the aluminum slot plate.  The snap-in idea was derived from scottmayson.   This body is designed for the eMinebea PG35L-048-USC0 motor.
MendelMax 1.5+ kits and printed parts are available for purchase at www.ultibots.com.
Alibre PE source files included.

The idler requires M3-40 bolts and use M4-12 bolts to secure to x-carriage.
Otherwise TrinityLabs vitamins are OK.
You will need to remove and drill out the support layers on the idler and body. This extruder works well with AlephObjects Supa-Flat X-Carriage
thingiverse.com/thing:10646
The bearing holders shown are:
http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:15205, the last one on the download list.
SDP_bearing_mount_for_y_axis__on_side_with_square_ends_and_fixed_holes_by_Simon.stl file. 09/08/12 - added a 30mm idler nut trap version with widened internal bearing cavity and eMinebea motor nut traps. 09/12/12 - added 1.75 filament versions

title: Parametric Lego Mindstorms NXT Phone Mount

description.text:
Parametric Lego Mindstorms NXT Phone Mount. This phone mount is designed for an Alcatel onetouch phone, however it should be adjustable to other phones by changing following parameters: pInnerHeight: Height of the phone (or a little bit less, so that the phone can be pull out of the mount easily)
pInnerWidth: Width of the phone
pInnerThickness: Thickness of the phone.
pOverlap: this value makes it possible to slide the phone into this phone mount; a value of 2 mm overlap should work fine.
